{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3123886,"name":"fovea1959","username":"fovea1959","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fovea1959/{size}/5301_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-12T02:42:23.612Z","cooked":"<p>I am trying to get a C++ example program for AprilTags stamped out quickly (trying to get examples into wpilib in time for the next version or so).</p>
<p>I have this in java:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">      AprilTagDetection[] detections = detector.detect(grayMat);
      for (AprilTagDetection detection : detections) {
        // process detection here
      }
</code></pre>
<p>I am having trouble writing the code to iterate over the detections in C++:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">      cv::Size s = grayMat.size();
      frc::AprilTagDetector::Results detections = detector.Detect (s.width, s.height, grayMat.data);

      // dumb Java guy doesn't know how to iterate over detections, this ain't right
      for (frc::AprilTagDetection detection : detections) {
        // process detection
      }
</code></pre>
<p>I haven’t looked at C++ for a long time; can someone help me get over this hurdle?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-01-12T02:43:10.030Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":13,"reads":99,"readers_count":98,"score":84.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":422599,"topic_slug":"need-help-translating-a-snippet-of-apriltags-java-to-c","display_username":"fovea1959","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":15648,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Herder of 3620 Programmers / LRI / CSA"},"post_url":"/t/need-help-translating-a-snippet-of-apriltags-java-to-c/422599/1","custom_user_title":"Herder of 3620 Programmers / LRI / CSA","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true,"can_vote":false},{"id":3123967,"name":"","username":"person4268","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/22d042/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-01-12T04:22:25.312Z","cooked":"<p>So, I haven’t actually tried this out (nor am I particularly knowledgeable in C++), but <a href="https://first.wpi.edu/wpilib/allwpilib/docs/release/cpp/classfrc_1_1_april_tag_detector_1_1_results.html#details" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">docs</a> say</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Each array element is a <strong>pointer</strong> to an AprilTagDetection.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In that case, I’d try this to dereference said pointer:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="cpp"><code class="lang-cpp">      for (const frc::AprilTagDetection&amp; detection : detections) {
        detection.GetId(); // Or whatever you want
      }
</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2023-01-12T04:22:25.312Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":75,"readers_count":74,"score":35.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":422599,"topic_slug":"need-help-translating-a-snippet-of-apriltags-java-to-c","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://first.wpi.edu/wpilib/allwpilib/docs/release/cpp/classfrc_1_1_april_tag_detector_1_1_results.html#details","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"WPILibC++: frc::AprilTagDetector::Results Class Reference","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":55016,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/need-help-translating-a-snippet-of-apriltags-java-to-c/422599/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1},{"id":"point_up","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3123983,"name":"Joseph Farkas","username":"MrRedness","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mrredness/{size}/229088_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-12T04:36:21.279Z","cooked":"<p>This might end up making each iteration have a const reference to the pointer, rather than derefencing, but don’t quote me on that. I’m fairly comfortable in c++ but I don’t pretend to understand the magic of for eac